{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/run(argc:argv:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"run","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"argc","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"argv"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5CChara","text":"CChar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">?>!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GIO","title":"run(argc:argv:)","externalID":"s:3GIO19ApplicationProtocolPAAE3run4argc4argvS2i_SpySpys4Int8VGSgGSgtF","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"run"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"argc","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"argv","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5CChara","text":"CChar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?>! = nil) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function is intended to be run from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"main()"},{"type":"text","text":" and its return value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is intended to be returned by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"main()"},{"type":"text","text":". Although you are expected to pass"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"code":"argc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"argv","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"main()"},{"text":" to this function, it is possible","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if "},{"code":"argv","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not available or commandline handling is not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"required.  Note that on Windows, ","type":"text"},{"code":"argc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"argv","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are ignored, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_win32_get_command_line()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called internally (for proper support"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of Unicode commandline arguments)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application"},{"text":" will attempt to parse the commandline arguments.  You","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can add commandline flags to the list of recognised options by way of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_application_add_main_option_entries()"},{"type":"text","text":".  After this, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onhandlelocaloptions(flags:handler:) signal is emitted, from which the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application can inspect the values of its ","type":"text"},{"code":"GOptionEntrys","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onhandlelocaloptions(flags:handler:) is a good place to handle options","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--version"},{"type":"text","text":", where an immediate reply from the local process is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"desired (instead of communicating with an already-running instance)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A [Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onhandlelocaloptions(flags:handler:) handler can stop further processing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"by returning a non-negative value, which then becomes the exit status of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the process."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"What happens next depends on the flags: if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"handlesCommandLine","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" was specified then the remaining","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"commandline arguments are sent to the primary instance, where a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/oncommandline(flags:handler:) signal is emitted.  Otherwise, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"remaining commandline arguments are assumed to be a list of files.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If there are no files listed, the application is activated via the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onactivate(flags:handler:) signal.  If there are one or more files, and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handlesOpen"},{"type":"text","text":" was specified then the files are opened"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"via the [Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onopen(flags:handler:) signal."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you are interested in doing more complicated local handling of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"commandline then you should implement your own ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","isActive":true},{"text":" subclass","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and override ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"local_command_line()"},{"type":"text","text":". In this case, you most likely want"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" from your "},{"code":"local_command_line()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implementation to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"suppress the default handling. See"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"#https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gapplication-example-cmdline2.c"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for an example.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If, after the above is done, the use count of the application is zero"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then the exit status is returned immediately.  If the use count is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-zero then the default main context is iterated until the use count"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"falls to zero, at which point 0 is returned."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the ","type":"text"},{"code":"isService","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is set, then the service will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"run for as much as 10 seconds with a use count of zero while waiting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the message that caused the activation to arrive.  After that,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if the use count falls to zero the application will exit immediately,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"except in the case that "},{"code":"g_application_set_inactivity_timeout()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function sets the prgname ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_set_prgname()"},{"text":"), if not already set,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the basename of argv[0].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Much like "},{"code":"g_main_loop_run()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this function will acquire the main context"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the duration that the application is running.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since 2.40, applications that are not explicitly flagged as services"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or launchers (ie: neither ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isService"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"isLauncher","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are given as flags) will check (from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default handler for local_command_line) if “–gapplication-service”","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"was given in the command line.  If this flag is present then normal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"commandline processing is interrupted and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"isService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is set.  This provides a “compromise”","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"solution whereby running an application directly from the commandline"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will invoke it in the normal way (which can be useful for debugging)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"while still allowing applications to be D-Bus activated in service","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"mode.  The D-Bus service file should invoke the executable with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“–gapplication-service” as the sole commandline argument.  This"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"approach is suitable for use by most graphical applications but"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"should not be used from applications like editors that need precise"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"control over when processes invoked via the commandline will exit and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"what their exit status will be.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Runs the application.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/run(argc:argv:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol"]]},"sections":[],"references":{"#https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/blob/HEAD/gio/tests/gapplication-example-cmdline2.c":{"url":"#https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gapplication-example-cmdline2.c","identifier":"#https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gapplication-example-cmdline2.c","type":"link","title":"gapplication-example-cmdline2.c","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"gapplication-example-cmdline2.c"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Application":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Application"}],"title":"Application","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core class for application support."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Application","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/application"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol/run(argc:argv:)":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/run(argc:argv:)","title":"run(argc:argv:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"run","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"argc"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"argv"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"CChar","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5CChara","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">?>!) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs the application."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/run(argc:argv:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ApplicationProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core class for application support."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol","title":"ApplicationProtocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ApplicationProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}